devdoc.details: Implementation of https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-721[ERC721] Non-Fungible Token Standard, including the Metadata and Enumerable extension. Built to optimize for lower gas during batch mints. Assumes serials are sequentially minted starting at 0 (e.g. 0, 1, 2, 3..). Does not support burning tokens to address(0). Assumes that an owner cannot have more than the 2**128 - 1 (max value of uint128) of supply

tokenOfOwnerByIndex(address,uint256).details: See {IERC721Enumerable-tokenOfOwnerByIndex}. This read function is O(totalSupply). If calling from a separate contract, be sure to test gas first. It may also degrade with extremely large collection sizes (e.g >> 10000), test for your use case.
